\pard\keep\keepn\s2\fi-576\li576\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\lang1033\b\f0\fs26 2.6\tab Detailed Description: Adversity Skill Points\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1\fs22 Depending on the harshness of the environment where your Protagonist grew up, he or she may gain \b Adversity Skill Point Picks\b0 . Each such pick provides a 20-point increase in rating for one skill from a pre-defined list. \par
\pard\sl276\slmult1 The number of Adversity Skill Point Picks your Protagonist receives depends on the Harshness Descriptor relevant to their particular upbringing:\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\f2\'b7\tab\b\f1 Normal(ish)\b0  upbringing: no Adversity Skill Point Picks\par
\f2\'b7\tab\b\f1 Harsh\b0  upbringing: 1 Adversity Skill Point Pick\par
\f2\'b7\tab\b\f1 Very Harsh\b0  upbringing: 2 Adversity Skill Point Picks\par
\pard\sl276\slmult1 Adversity Skill Point Picks can \i ONLY\i0  be spent to increase ratings in the following list of setting-specific adversity skills: \par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\lang3081 First Aid, Military Training (type), Regional Lore (type), or Survival (type)\lang1033 .\par
You can pick the same skill more than once.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s2\fi-576\li576\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0\fs26 2.7\tab Detailed Description: Resources\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1\fs22 Every Protagonist has a Resources rating between 0 and 20. This number is an abstraction that represents the size, value, and utility of the \b personal pool of resources\b0  to which he or she has ready access. A Protagonist who is \ldblquote wealthy\rdblquote  in a material sense will have a high Resources rating, since they have personal ownership \endash  and hence access \endash  to more things. Conversely, someone who is destitute and forced to carry their meagre belongings on their back will probably have a very low Resources rating. The definition of what constitutes \ldblquote wealth\rdblquote  and \ldblquote valuable resources\rdblquote  might vary depending on the game setting, but the Resources rating is a handy abstract rating which compares the magnitude of the Protagonist\rquote s material possessions against other people\rquote s. \par
The Resources rating represents a pool of previously unspecified items \i in addition to\i0  any named pieces of equipment that appears on the Protagonist\rquote s character sheet.\par
There are two ways in which Resources ratings can become important during a game of \i Cthulhu Eternal\i0 :\par
\pard\fi-357\li714\sa200\sl276\slmult1 1.\tab The rating can be used as a measure of status and wealth which dictates how Non-Player Characters react to the Protagonists; a Protagonist who has a sizeable cache of resources might find NPCs more willing to listen to what he or she has to say \'85 or alternatively more likely to want to take some of those resources away.\par
2.\tab Game encounters may involve challenges which can be overcome through possession of particular \endash  possibly obscure \endash  items or resources; a Protagonist who fossicks through his or her trove of (unnamed) personal items may locate just the thing that is needed. Usually this requires a successful \b Resources test\b0  (a 1D100 roll against \b Resources\b0  \b\'d7\b0  \b 5\b0 ). \par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 A Protagonist\rquote s Resources rating may change during play as especially significant items are pulled from the \ldblquote bag of tricks\rdblquote , items are destroyed, or new equipment caches are picked over for useful additions.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 2.7.1\tab Determining the Starting Resources rating\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1 Your Protagonist\rquote s Archetype determines the starting value for his or her Resources rating; it is a number listed as part of the Archetype description.\par
\pard If you would prefer this value to be higher, you have the option to \ldblquote trade-in\rdblquote  one or more \b BONUS SKILL POINT\b0  picks (see page \lang3081 26\lang1033 ). For the first such skill pick traded-in, your Protagonist receives a +5 boost to Resources rating. Each additional pick you trade in beyond the first, grants your Protagonist a further +2 boost to Resources. You may sacrifice as many skill picks as you wish, although each will reduce your opportunities to round-out your Protagonist with extra skills during a later step of Protagonist creation.\par
Alternatively, if you would prefer to play a Protagonist who is entirely bereft of resources (i.e., has a Resources rating of 0), you can choose to do so and in return receive one extra Bonus Skill Point Pick for later use.\par
\pard\sl276\slmult1\b Rating\tab\tab What the Rating Represents\par
\pard\b0 0 \tab\tab No ownership of any item of value or function. Penury. Near starvation.\par
1-4\tab\tab Owns only basic and valueless items; barely enough to eke out a basic life. Always hungry.\par
5-8\tab\tab Owns a sparse collection of valuable or useful items, some in terrible condition. Sometimes hungry.\par
9-12\tab\tab Owns a modest cache of valuable, useful items. Usually has basic food.\par
\pard\fi-1440\li1440 13-16\tab Owns a fair stock of low-grade valuable items. Occasional access to superior food.\par
17-18\tab Owns an impressive collection of useful gear; considered wealthy / well-resourced. Regular access to superior food\par
19\tab The envy of most people; owns numerous sought-after items of impressive function. Access to the best food and beverages.\par
\pard\fi-1440\li1440\sa200\sl276\slmult1 20+\tab Access to unparalleled quantities of valuable or useful items. A stockpile of wealth. Choice of any available food, in any quantity.\par
\pard If you need to know how your Resources Rating translates to financial wealth, consult the table in the \b BUYING EQUIPMENT\b0  section (page \lang3081 60\lang1033 ).\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 2.7.2\tab Permanent Resources, Resources At-Hand, and Resource Checks\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1 The full value established above is called the Protagonist\rquote s \b Permanent Resources\b0  rating, since it measures the sum total of everything he or she owns \endash  regardless of where it is kept. \par
Carrying around a lot of bulky equipment everywhere is usually not practical, so Protagonists with significant Resources ratings (7+ points) will usually need to \b stow\b0  some of their junk in a vehicle or on a pack animal. Those with even more resources will need to \b store \b0 the overflow in a fixed \lquote home base\rquote  location. \par
