\lang1033\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s2\fi-576\li576\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0\fs26 2.10\tab Detailed Description: Skills\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1\fs22 A skill represents expertise gained with intensive training or study. If you make a skill roll, your Protagonist is doing something that would leave untrained people lost. \par
\lang3081 Anyone can attempt a DEX\'d75 test to keep their footing in the cabin of a Zeppelin madly buffeted through the clouds; only someone who\rquote s been trained in the proper Pilot skill can steer the battered airship away from the grasping, tentacled thing tearing at its flank.\lang1033  \par
Roll your Protagonist\rquote s skill or lower on 1D100 to succeed at using the skill under dire circumstances. Skills improve through practice and experience.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 2.10.1\tab Base Rating\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1 Every skill lists its base rating. If a skill has a base rating of 1% or greater, anyone can attempt to use it. A skill at 0% can\rquote t be used at all. No skill can be higher than 99%.\par
\pard\b Rating\tab\tab What the Rating Represents\par
\b0 01% to 19% \tab Dabbler.\par
20% to 29% \tab A dedicated hobbyist; with a foreign language you can have rudimentary conversations.\par
30% to 39% \tab Equivalent of a dedicated basic training.\par
\pard\fi-1440\li1440 40% to 59% \tab Equivalent of a dedicated advanced training or years of practical experience; with 50% in a foreign language you have native fluency.\par
\pard 60% to 79% \tab Decades of experience, or equivalent of the highest level of advanced training.\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 80% to 99% \tab A lifetime\rquote s pursuit or equivalent of multiple related training qualifications.\par
