\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 2.10.2\tab How Skills Work\par
\pard\cf0\b0\f1 For details of specific skills, see the listing in \b SKILL DESCRIPTIONS\b0  starting on page \lang3081 29\lang1033 . \par
When your Protagonist uses a skill, sometimes you roll dice and sometimes you don\rquote t.\par
\b USING A SKILL WITHOUT A ROLL:\b0  When circumstances are calm and controlled, you don\rquote t roll dice to have your Protagonist use a skill; the Game Moderator just needs to know how high your Protagonist\rquote s rating is. \par
\lang3081 For example, safely driving a shiny new Packard roadster when things are calm might simply require a certain amount in the Drive skill.\lang1033  \par
Using a skill without rolling means randomness is not a factor. It\rquote s about having the right skill, looking in the right place, and asking the right questions. The more subtle the clue, the higher the skill your Protagonist must have to figure it out.\par
\b USING A SKILL WITH A ROLL:\b0  Roll skill dice only when the outcome is in doubt. That usually means there\rquote s a crisis or the circumstances are not under your Protagonist\rquote s control. The higher the skill rating, the better your Protagonist\rquote s chance of success. For details, see \b USING SKILLS\b0  on page \lang3081 37\lang1033 .\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 2.10.3\tab Common Knowledge\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1 Most Protagonists picked up some basic knowledge as they grew up. Because of this, they have some basic understanding of common things like how their society works and what types of jobs do what; and some basic abilities like how to flee danger. These don\rquote t require specific skills. Skills represents deep, specialized training or education, but Protagonists can sometimes get by on common knowledge. Calling on common knowledge requires an \b INT\'d75\b0  test or having a certain level of INT. Charming someone with unskilled art is usually a \b CHA\b0  or \b DEX\b0  test. Other efforts use other stats. The Game Moderator decides whether a task requires the general ability of a stat or the specialization of a skill.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 2.10.4\tab Improving Skills\par
\pard\cf0\b0\f1 We learn from failure. If your Protagonist has at least 1% in a skill (any except Unnatural), it can improve when your Protagonists attempts to use it and \i fails\i0 . Gaining an entirely new skill requires special training (see \b DOWNTIME \b0 on page \lang3081 76\lang1033 ).\par
On the character sheet, next to every skill except Unnatural, there is a check box. When your Protagonist tries to use a skill and fails, put a checkmark in that skill\rquote s box. At the end of each game session, add 1D4 percentage point to every skill that has a check next to it and erase the check.\par
\b FAILING WITHOUT ROLLING:\b0  If your Protagonist attempts a challenging task that requires a certain level of skill but not a roll, and fails because the task requires more skill than your Protagonist has, put a check in the box.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 2.10.5\tab Skill Descriptions\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\b0\i Administration\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 10%\par
A knowledge of how bureaucracies work and what kinds of forms, paperwork, journals, etc. it invariably generates. Use it to sift through detailed financial records or proceedings of club meetings to find that one quirky point that just doesn\rquote t seem to fit the usual pattern. \par
Use this skill to rapidly navigate your way adeptly through administrative records to find what\rquote s important. Note that this skill is primarily about interpreting information you have; if you need to actively go out and track down books, records, etc. that would be covered by the \b Research\b0  skill.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Alertness\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 20%\par
Alertness detects danger. Use it to hear a safety being weapon being readied, to understand the mumbling on the other side of a wall, to spot a concealed item hidden under a jacket, or to catch someone who is trying to escape notice using Stealth.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Anthropology\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 0%\par
The study of living human cultures. Use it to understand morals, religious beliefs, customs, and mores, and to identify (but not translate) obscure languages. Where History is about the distant past and Archeology studies physical artifacts, Anthropology is about the behaviors of living cultures and how they relate to each other and the past.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Appraise\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 10%\par
The ability to quickly determine the true (intrinsic) value of an item. This is an important skill in ensuring that bartering exchange deals are favorable to you. It is also helpful in know what items or resources others might be willing to trade to obtain.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Archeology\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 0%\par
The study of physical remains of human cultures. Use it to analyze a ruined structure to determine useful information about its purpose long ago or the circumstances of its destruction. Where Anthropology is about living cultures and History is a broad study of the past, Archeology discerns meaning from the artifacts left behind.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Art (Type)\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 0%\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 Expertise at creating or performing a work that sways emotions and opinions. It also encompasses knowledge of techniques and trends in your field, and the ability tell a particular creator\rquote s real work from a fake. Anyone can draw a rough sketch; the Art skill reflects knowledge, practice, and talent. Each type of Art is a separate skill: Acting, Dance, Forgery, Music, Poetry, Sculpture, Singing, Storytelling, etc.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Athletics\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 30%\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 Your Protagonist trains to get the most out of his or her strength and agility. Strength and Dexterity cover raw physical power and manual dexterity; the Athletics skill represents long practice doing things like running, jumping, climbing, and throwing.\par
\pard\sl276\slmult1 Use Athletics to:\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\f2\'b7\tab\f1 Outrun someone (see \b OPPOSED TESTS\b0  on page \lang3081 41\lang1033 ).\par
\f2\'b7\tab\f1 Jump an intimidating gap.\par
\f2\'b7\tab\f1 Climb in a crisis.\par
\f2\'b7\tab\f1 Land safely in a fall of up to three yards.\par
\f2\'b7\tab\f1 Hit a target with a thrown knife or put a grenade exactly on target.\par
\f2\'b7\tab\f1 Catch something without warning, such as intercepting a thrown grenade.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Charm\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 20%\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 Changing someone else\rquote s viewpoint or convincing them to do something for you through guile, cunning, \ldblquote buttering-up\rdblquote , or other such subtle techniques. It\rquote s not about threatening them (that\rquote s covered by the \b Harangue\b0  skill) or using cold logic to convince them (that\rquote s \b Persuade\b0 ) but covers all those other soft-touch methods. With Charm you might be able to connect with an individual on a more personal level \endash  maybe even seduce them \endash  and such changes can become long-held attitudes or beliefs. If the target of the skill starts from an antagonistic viewpoint, some form of OPPOSED TEST will probably be needed to overcome their negative impression. \par
\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Craft (Type)\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 0%\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 Making and repairing sophisticated tools and structures. A job that most people could figure out does not require the Craft skill, only an INT or DEX test. Use Craft for specialized work that needs training: Craft (Mechanic) to get a broken apparatus working \emdash  or to sabotage one beyond repair; Craft (Locksmith) to open a lock without a key, and so on. \par
A common specialization is \b Craft (Jury-Rigging)\b0  which represents an ability to create lash-ups of equipment to perform a function when the proper tool for the job is unavailable. \par
The Game Moderator decides whether a task requires Craft. Each Craft type is a separate skill: Blacksmith, Carpenter, Farmer, Jury-Rigging, Locksmith, Mechanic, etc.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Disguise\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 10%\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 Alter your Protagonist\rquote s appearance, voice, posture, body language, and mannerisms to avoid recognition without drawing attention.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Dodge\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 30%\par
\pard Evading danger through instinct and reflexes. Use Dodge to avoid an attack. Against firearms and explosives, Dodge is only useful to get to cover (see \b DODGING RANGED ATTACKS\b0  on page \lang3081 48\lang1033 ).\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Drive\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 20%\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 Handling any ground-based vehicle or conveyance safely in a crisis. Unless the Game Moderator says otherwise, every Protagonist can drive safely in normal conditions. Use this skill to keep a vehicle safe in a tense pursuit or on dangerous terrain.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Firearms\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 20%\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 Safe and accurate shooting with common firearms in combat. Use it to hit a target despite the adrenaline, panic, and shock of violence interfering with hand-eye coordination.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 First Aid\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 10%\par
\pard The initial treatment and stabilization of injuries. Use it to help a character recover lost Hit Points. By comparison, Surgery corrects a severe wound and Medicine ensures long-term recovery. (See \b HEALING\b0  on page \lang3081 49\lang1033 .)\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Foreign Language (Type)\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 0%\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 Fluency in another language. Each foreign language is a distinct skill. Having 20% allows halting conversations; at 50% your Protagonist speaks and reads like a native. The greater the skill, the greater the complexity of the information your Protagonist comprehends and the less time it takes. You don\rquote t need to roll a Foreign Language skill unless the Game Moderator says the situation is exceptionally difficult.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Harangue\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 10%\par
\pard\sa240\sl276\slmult1 The art of browbeating someone into agreeing with your point of view or agreeing to do something you want them to do. This technique is not a subtle attempt to engage with their good nature (that\rquote s covered by the Charm skill) or their logical reason (that\rquote s Persuade) \endash  instead it\rquote s all about bluster, shouting, and threats. But sometimes these can be more successful than other techniques, although the individuals on the receiving end are unlikely to enjoy the interaction quite so much.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Heavy Machinery\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 10%\par
Safe operation of a tractor, crane, thresher, steam train, or other big machine in a crisis.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 History\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 10%\par
Uncovering facts and theories about human antiquity. Use it to remember or find a key fact about the distant past, recognize an obscure reference, or comb through records that nobody without your deep education could find. While Anthropology is about living cultures and Archaeology studies the meaning of ancient relics, History is a broad study of humanity.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Insight\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 10%\par
Insight obtains information about a person \emdash  especially information the subject would rather conceal \emdash  through observation, conversation, or examining patterns of behavior and relationships. Use Insight to recognize signs of dishonesty from verbal cues and body language, gauge attitude and intentions, cultivate sources of information about a subject, determine what it would take to get a subject to cooperate, or recognize clues of what a subject wants to conceal. \par
\pard Insight can notice signs of mental illness but Psychoanalyze would be needed to assist with a specific malady. A subject who deliberately tries to deceive your Protagonist can attempt an opposed test comparing their Persuade against your Protagonist\rquote s Insight (see \b OPPOSED TESTS\b0  on page \lang3081 41\lang1033 ).\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Law (Type)\f7\fs24\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1\fs22 Base Rating: 0%\lang3081\par
\lang1033 Use this skill to understand and manipulate the power structures that exist within society, to either influence outcomes or bullshit your Protagonist\rquote s way out of trouble. \par
Different societies have their own systems of law \endash  the understanding of each is a separate skill. Because all societies are based on common human behavior, you can attempt to use your Law skill at \i half\i0  chance to navigate the vagaries of a an entirely new and unfamiliar social order. \par
\page\cf1\i\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\f0 Medicine\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 0%\par
\pard The study and treatment of injury and illness. Use it to diagnose the cause of an injury, disease, or poisoning, identify abnormalities such as toxins or diseases, identify the cause and approximate time of death, identify a dead person\rquote s last meal, or prescribe proper long-term care. By comparison, First Aid keeps a patient alive until surgery is possible, and Surgery corrects a severe wound. (See \b HEALING\b0  on page \lang3081 49\lang1033 ).\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Melee Weapons\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 30%\par
Lethal use of melee weapons in combat. Use it to hurt or kill an opponent with a knife, axe, club, or other hand-held weapon.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Military Training (Type)\f7\fs24\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1\fs22 Base Rating: 0%\lang3081\par
\pard\sa240\sl276\slmult1\lang1033 Many people spend a part of their careers in some form of military service to a crown or other empire \endash  whether as part of an army or navy, or even on boats in coastal waters. A great many people are also employed in the giant bureaucracy that keeps the military supplied and functioning. This skill represents first-hand training and experience obtained through time spent in one such military service. Use it to apply military tactics or strategies to a situation, to recall specific details about a particular military unit or corps, or to know your way around common military-issue equipment.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Natural World\f7\fs24\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1\fs22 Base Rating: 10%\par
The common understanding of the natural world as practiced by farmers, fishermen, and others who make a living based upon the changing patterns of the weather, tides, etc. It also covers the broad understanding of the natural habits of animals, as well as the different uses of specific plant species. Use this skill to determine whether observed behavior of natural forces or creatures is consistent with \ldblquote normal\rdblquote  or common patterns, or not.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Navigate\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 10%\par
Finding your way quickly with maps, charts and tables, orienteering, compass, or dead reckoning.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Occult\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 10%\par
The study of the supernatural as understood by human traditions, including things like magick, folklore, and secret societies. Use Occult to examine and deduce the intent of a ritual, or to identify occult traditions, groups, grimoires, tools, symbols, or legends. Occult can never tell a Protagonist what\rquote s genuinely unnatural and what\rquote s just superstition or mythology. That\rquote s the province of the Unnatural skill.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Persuade\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 20%\par
Changing another\rquote s deeply held decision or desire. Use Persuade to get your Protagonist\rquote s way when the subject is so stubborn, what your Protagonist wants is so valuable, or the deception is so flagrant that Charisma isn\rquote t enough. \par
\pard With Persuade, your Protagonist might convince a witness that what she saw was innocuous and not unnatural, talk a compound leader into helping you cover up an outbreak to avoid a mass panic, or draw useful information out of an unwilling subject. This skill also allows your Protagonist to resist persuasion and interrogation in opposed Persuade rolls (see \b OPPOSED TESTS\b0  on page \lang3081 41\lang1033 ).\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Pilot (Type)\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 0%\par
Piloting, navigating, and captaining waterborne, or airborne vehicles. Use it to keep a vessel safe in a crisis, such as through a storm or in a dangerous pursuit. Each vessel type is a separate skill: Airplane, Airship, Small Boat, Ship, etc.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Psychoanalyze\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 10%\par
\pard The diagnosis and treatment of mental illness. Use it to identify a mental disorder, help a patient recover, talk someone down when a disorder begins to take over, and treat mental illness in the long term. You cannot use Psychoanalysis on yourself. Using Psychoanalysis to aid someone who suffered exposure to Cthulhu Mythos forces might cost the therapist SAN; see \b THREATS TO SAN\b0  on page \lang3081 66\lang1033 .\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Regional Lore (Type)\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 0%\par
\pard\sa240\sl276\slmult1 Most educated people know a little bit about every place, but if you\rquote ve spent a long time living in (or studying) a specific region you learn so much more. This skill represents a deep understanding of the people, places, and common practices that are unique to one particular region. Use it to recall folktales that villagers tell, unique local words, or unusual ruins and earthworks found in the region. It can also cover quirky superstitions and rites that are particular to the region. \par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Research\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 10%\par
The ability to find specific information in a large repository or buried in files, records, or ledger books. Use this skill to navigate a library catalogue system, pull out buried details in account records, or otherwise locate whatever relevant information lies buried. \par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Ride\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 10%\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 Handling, training, and riding an animal\emdash horses, donkeys, camels, whatever. Use it to keep safe on an animal in a crisis and to keep riding animals safe, calm, and healthy.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Science (Type)\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 0%\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 The deep study of the processes of the world. This is more than common schooling; anyone can attempt an INT test to remember facts from whatever (rudimentary) schooling they received. Science is used to find a key insight about the way the universe works \emdash  or at least, the way it\rquote s supposed to work. Each Science is a separate skill: Astronomy, Biology, Botany, Chemistry, Engineering, Forensics, Genetics, Geology, Mathematics, Meteorology, Nutrition, Physics, Radio, Zoology, etc.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Search\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 20%\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 Finding things that are concealed or obscured from plain sight. Searching an abandoned dwelling may not require the Search skill, only time and effort, or a sufficiently high INT. Use Search to find an object that was hidden with the Stealth skill or is otherwise so well hidden or disguised that it needs an expert. The Game Moderator may roll the Search attempt, so you don\rquote t know whether your Protagonist succeeded or failed.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Social Etiquette\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 10%\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 Good manners cost nothing, or so they say, and in this era they are an essential part of \lquote civilized\rquote  society. One simple faux pas at a dinner party can make you a laughingstock, or have you ejected from a prestigious club. Use this skill to know what complex rules of etiquette might apply in any given situation and be prepared to follow them instinctively when you need to. Alternative, it may be used to spot situations where someone else is failing to follow one of society\rquote s many little rules. \par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Stealth\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 10%\par
\pard Concealing your presence or activities. Use it to hide a weapon, camouflage a position, conceal an occult amulet, pick a pocket, move silently, follow without being seen, or blend into a crowd. A Protagonist attempting Stealth can be detected only by an opposing Alertness or Search skill (see \b OPPOSED TESTS\b0  on page \lang3081 41\lang1033 ).\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Streetwise (Type)\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 0%\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 In cities and towns, there is an entirely separate \lquote society\rquote  that exists between the criminal classes, the poor, and everybody else that the high-and-mighty would prefer to believe don\rquote t exist. In fact, there are many different sub-cultures and groups who make up this (largely invisible) under-class. This skill represents detailed knowledge of one such strata of society. It includes extensive details about contacts \endash  who does what and where one might go to obtain any kind of illicit goods or services common to that group. Some groupings may be region-based (e.g., \ldblquote the docks\rdblquote ), while others represent broad categories of people or services (e.g., \ldblquote smugglers and bootleggers\rdblquote ).\lang3081\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\lang1033\i\f0 Surgery\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 0%\par
\pard The treatment of an injury or abnormality, by invasive means. By comparison, First Aid keeps a patient alive until surgery is possible, and Medicine ensures long term recovery. (See \b HEALING\b0  on page \lang3081 49\lang1033 )\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Survival (Type)\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 10%\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 Knowledge of the natural world. Use it to plan an expedition, predict weather, recognize when fauna or flora are unusual, use the environment to gather other information, or find food, water, and shelter. Each type of Survival is its own skill. Common types are Desert, Jungle, Tundra, Urban.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Swim\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 20%\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 Most Protagonists can swim for leisure. Use the Swim skill in a dangerous crisis: going a long distance in choppy water, keeping a friend from drowning, or getting to a boat before the tentacled thing below grabs you.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Track\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 10%\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 Use this to locate the tracks of a specific creature or person and follow them. A test must be made to locate the trail and then again once every ten minutes they are being followed. Penalties or bonuses may apply depending on how long it was since the tracks were made, what the ground is like, what the weather conditions have been since the tracks were made, etc.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Unarmed Combat\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 20%\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 Self-defense. A fight between untrained combatants often involves more shoving and shouting than real violence. Use Unarmed Combat to hurt or kill an opponent with your Protagonist\rquote s bare hands (or feet, elbows, teeth, or head).\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Unnatural\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 0%\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 Knowledge of the fundamental, mind-shattering secrets of the universe. The things that slithered in the dark corners of the world and the cosmos beyond. Use it to remember, recognize, or research facts about the things humans consider unnatural. This goes far beyond the occult, because the Unnatural skill represents things that are real. Use it to sift through the darkest parts of myth and folklore and recognize which of it is true. \par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Use Gadgets\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Base Rating: 0%\par
Nobody needs to make a skill roll to use devices and technologies that are in common use in the era and setting of the game. However, making effective use of highly-specialized or technical apparatus is a different question. In the hands on the untrained, such devices are at best useless, and at worst dangerous. Use Gadgets is an umbrella skill allowing your Protagonist to successfully use all manner of common technical devices.\par
