\b PARTIALLY BLINDED:\b0  The Protagonist suffers a \u8722?20% penalty to all tests requiring good eyesight.\par
\b PARTIALLY DEAFENED:\b0  The Protagonist suffers a \u8722?20% penalty to all tests requiring good hearing.\par
\b ARM CRIPPLED OR SEVERED:\b0  The Protagonist suffers a \u8722?20% penalty to all tests requiring two hands.\par
\b LEG CRIPPLED OR SEVERED:\b0  The Protagonist suffers a \u8722?20% penalty to all tests requiring movement.\cell\row\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 4.4.1\tab Healing\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1 There are four types of healing: \i Resuscitation, Stabilization, Treatment, \i0 and \i Recuperation\i0 .\par
\b RESUSCITATION:\b0  Sometimes it\rquote s possible to resuscitate a dead character. If the Game Moderator says resuscitation is possible, someone must make a \b First Aid\b0  test. This must occur within a number of minutes after death equal to the victim\rquote s CON score. If it succeeds, it restores 1D4 HP (doubled for a critical success) and allows the patient to recover. If First Aid fails, the victim dies and may not be resuscitated.\par
\b STABILIZATION:\b0  Stabilizing a wounded character with a successful \b First Aid\b0  test immediately heals 1D4 HP. A critical success doubles the amount healed; a fumble \i inflicts \i0 1D4 damage. Once your Protagonist receives first aid, success or failure, the Protagonist can\rquote t benefit from it again until he or she suffers damage again.\par
\b TREATMENT:\b0  Treatment is professional care in a clean, calm location with extensive tools and healing supplies. \par
\lang3081 A doctor can attempt a Surgery or Medicine test once per week: Surgery for critical care of severe wounds; Medicine for poison, disease, and ongoing healing. If treatment succeeds, the patient recovers 1D4 HP. This is doubled with a critical, while a fumble inflicts 1D4 HP damage. At the Game Moderator\rquote s discretion, having worn-out tools or poor quality medicines may incur a penalty.\lang1033\par
\b RECUPERATION:\b0  Over time, the human body repairs itself. A patient who rests in a safe place with proper food and water can attempt a \b CON\'d75\b0  test once per day to recover 1 HP (in addition to any HP recovered due to medical treatment). On a critical success, the patient regains 1D4; on a fumble, the patient loses 1 HP.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 4.4.2\tab Complications\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1 After treatment, and until the patient heals all lost Hit Points, undertaking strenuous activity (any physical stat or skill test) inflicts 1D4 HP damage as sutures rip, broken bones shift, or fever sets in.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 4.4.3\tab Recovering Stat Points\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1 Unless the Game Moderator says otherwise, temporarily lost stat points are restored at 1 point per day.\par
