\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1\fs22 Some items that the Protagonists want to obtain might not be easy to obtain \endash  either because they are restricted in some way, especially scarce, or illegal. Alternatively, the items might be available, but priced such that the Protagonist simply can\rquote t afford them. In such situations, the only recourse might be to scrounge around to see if the items can be \lquote liberated\rquote  from somewhere. This might involve sifting through discarded items to find pieces that are good enough to function as needed, and perhaps lashing them together to make more complex equipment.\par
If a Protagonist wants to obtain a resource that isn\rquote t available to them via simple means, there are two ways:\par
\pard\fi-360\li765\sa200\sl276\slmult1 1.\tab By rummaging through the stockpile of belongings that constitute his or her personal \lquote resources\rquote , or\par
2.\tab Searching the environment to try to locate an abandoned or unclaimed supply of that resource.\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 Each of these methods uses a different game mechanic. \par
The former is a use of the Protagonist\rquote s \b Resources\b0  rating, while the latter is a use of his or her \lang3081\b Search\lang1033\b0  skill.\par
In both cases, the difficulty of the test to locate a usable item depends on the scarcity of the item being sought, as well as:\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\f2\'b7\tab\b\f1 [For rummaging the resource pool]\b0  \endash  whether the item is small enough to realistically be carried around from place to place.\par
\f2\'b7\tab\b\f1 [For scavenging] \endash\b0  whether the location being searched is a likely or unlikely place for such resources to have been stored or abandoned.\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 The results of a test can indicate that an item has been discovered, or describe utter failure of the search/rummaging. However even if the roll is successful there is no guarantee that the resource discovered will be in good condition \endash  the discovered item might be heavily worn or maybe even utter junk (see box nearby).\par
