\pard\keep\keepn\s2\fi-576\li576\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0\fs26 7.5\tab Insanity and Disorders\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1\fs22 Protagonists who lose excessive SAN lose control of themselves, suffering insanity and mental disorders.\par
\pard\b TEMPORARY INSANITY (PAGE \lang3081 69\lang1033 ):\b0  A Protagonist who loses 5 or more points of SAN in a \i single roll \i0 suffers \i temporary insanity\i0 .\par
\b DISORDER (PAGE \lang3081 70\lang1033 ):\b0  Every time your Protagonist\rquote s SAN is reduced to his or her Breaking Point (see \b DERIVED ATTRIBUTES\b0  on page \lang3081 10\lang1033 ), he or she gains a new \i disorder\i0 . Immediately reset your Protagonist\rquote s Breaking Point to your Protagonist\rquote s current SAN minus POW. Even if SAN rises back above the old Breaking Point, the disorder and the new Breaking Point remain.\par
\b PERMANENT INSANITY (PAGE \lang3081 73\lang1033 ):\b0  If your Protagonist hits 0 SAN, he or she suffers \i permanent insanity \i0 and becomes the property of the Game Moderator.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s2\fi-576\li576\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0\fs26 7.6\tab Temporary Insanity\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1\fs22 In a moment of overwhelming stress \emdash  after losing 5 or more SAN \i in a single roll\i0  \emdash  your Protagonist loses self-control. We call it temporary insanity. For a short time, you cannot control your Protagonist\rquote s actions. Your Protagonist\rquote s primitive brain switches to pure panic, with one of three possible responses: \i Flee, Struggle, \i0 or \i Submit\i0 .\par
Work with the Game Moderator to determine which stance your Protagonist takes. Each is more likely in some circumstances than others. \par
If the circumstances are calm, it may be possible to talk your Protagonist down from temporary insanity.\par
Such attempts are tests of the \lang3081\b Psychoanalyze\lang1033  \b0 skill. \par
In the absence of anything like that, your Protagonist loses control until the insanity runs its course.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 7.6.1\tab Flee\par
\pard\cf0\b0\f1 Your Protagonist must move away from the SAN-affecting stimulus at top speed in any direction. Your Protagonist must do this for a number of turns equal to his or her CON, whereupon your Protagonist falls to the ground exhausted (see \b EXHAUSTION\b0  on page \lang3081 43\lang1033 ), or until your Protagonist feels \lquote safe\rquote , whichever happens first. This is a common reaction against Unnatural and Violence SAN threats.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 7.6.2\tab Struggle\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1 This is lashing out randomly at the nearest threat, no matter how insurmountable it might be. Once this course is set upon, your Protagonist has no choice but to fight until he or she is killed, unconscious, or restrained. This is a common reaction against Helplessness and Violence SAN threats.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 7.6.3\tab Submit\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1 This is shutting down or passing out from shock. If conscious, your Protagonist is catatonic and paralyzed until the Game Moderator decides he or she snaps out of it. When your Protagonist comes to, it\rquote s likely he or she has suppressed the trauma that caused his or her collapse. Remembering details requires an \b INT\'d75\b0  test and is terribly stressful. This is a common reaction against Unnatural and Helplessness SAN threats.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 7.6.4\tab Understanding the Unnatural\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1 Whenever your Protagonist goes temporarily insane or develops a disorder due to an encounter with the Unnatural, he or she also gains some deeper understanding of the true nature of reality. \par
If your Protagonist had no prior knowledge of the Cthulhu Mythos (i.e., has an Unnatural skill rating of 0), such an experience causes him or her to gain +5 percentiles in the Unnatural skill. Even if they already knew about the Unnatural, such an experience grants a further +1 percentile to the Unnatural skill. \par
This increase also serves to reduce the Protagonist\rquote s maximum SAN (and if current SAN is higher than this value, also causes it to drop to the new maximum).\par
