\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 7.10.4\tab Getting Help with Mental Illness\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1 After the adventure your Protagonist can attempt to recuperate with empathetic colleagues or by focusing on his or her Bonds; the things that give your Protagonist strength (see \b DOWNTIME\b0 , below). Any such recovery can never push the Protagonist\rquote s current SAN any higher than his or her \b Recovery SAN\b0  (POW\'d75), or \b Maximum SAN\b0 , whichever is lower.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 7.10.5\tab Pursuing Personal Goals or Caring for Individuals\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1 Time spent between adventures doing things that naturally reassert your Protagonist\rquote s \lquote normal\rquote  life can slightly improve his or her SAN (see \b DOWNTIME\b0 , below). This can only increase current SAN up to his or her \b Recovery SAN\b0  (POW\'d75), or \b Maximum SAN\b0 , whichever is lower.\par
\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s1\fi-431\li431\sb240\sl276\slmult1\cf1\b\f0\fs28 8.0\tab Downtime\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1\fs22 Games of \i Cthulhu Eternal\i0  should feature occasional scenes that \cf3 focus on Protagonists\rquote  everyday lives. These short vignettes should last no more than a few minutes. Typically, they occur between adventures, but the Game Moderator always decides when and whether one is appropriate. These vignettes are a chance to explore the most important things in your Protagonist\rquote s life \emdash  and to see whether those things are deteriorating thanks to the Protagonist\rquote s experience of the secret horrors of the world.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s2\fi-576\li576\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0\fs26 8.1\tab What Changed\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1\fs22 In a downtime vignette, take stock of what changed for your Protagonist in the last adventure.\par
\b BONDS DAMAGED OR BROKEN:\b0  Describe how each relationship has deteriorated.\par
\b PERMANENT INJURIES:\b0  Describe what they look like.\par
\b DISORDERS GAINED:\b0  Did your Protagonist hit the Breaking Point during the adventure? Now\rquote s the time for the Game Moderator to decide what disorder the Protagonist gains. \par
\b COMMUNITY:\b0  If your Protagonist misused his or her contacts, authority, or resources from his or her home community, describe how actions during the adventure may have impacted your Protagonist\rquote s reputation or standing. Does this impact any Community Bonds?\par
\b JUSTICE\b0 : Did your Protagonist break the rules of the local community? Does that impact any Individual or Community Bonds?\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s2\fi-576\li576\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0\fs26 8.2\tab Personal Pursuits\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1\fs22 For the vignette, the player chooses one of the following pursuits. Describe how your Protagonist is pursuing it, and roll the appropriate stat, skill, or SAN test to resolve it.\par
Choose from these pursuits:\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 8.2.1\tab Fulfill Responsibilities to Individuals\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1 If your Protagonist focuses on day-to-day obligations and relationships, describe something the Protagonist is doing to support an Individual Bond. Roll a SAN test. Success improves the Individual Bond by 1D6 (up to your Protagonist\rquote s CHA); a critical success also adds 1 SAN (up to your \b Recovery SAN\b0 ). Failure adds 1 to the Bond. A fumble means some disastrous conflict reduces the Individual Bond by 1D4 and your SAN by 1. Describe how the relationship has improved because of your Protagonist\rquote s efforts or worsened despite them.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 8.2.2\tab Reorganizing and Replenishing Personal Resources\par
\pard\cf0\b0\f1 As described in \b\caps Replenishing Resources, Removing Checkmarks\b0\caps0  (page \lang3081 23\lang1033 ), if your Protagonist actively drew from his or her personal pool of Resources during an adventure, there will be check marks on the character sheet to record this. By investing some downtime (half a day or more) to reorganize or replenish your stash of resources, all such checks marks can be erased. Describe the lengths your Protagonist goes to tidy up or restock.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 8.2.3\tab Gaining Favor of the Community at Large\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1 Your Protagonist may choose to spend time attempting to improve his or her status within a group or society, as represented by a Community Bond he or she \b\i already has\b0\i0 . This may involve influencing key individuals to build a support-base or working hard to solve the community\rquote s problems and earn their respect. \par
A major investment of time warrants a SAN test \endash  success means that your Protagonist\rquote s actions have drawn the attention of key people in the community. A fumbled SAN roll means that some terrible error of judgement by your Protagonist creates a negative reaction: this reduces the bond value by -1D3 and causes a loss of 1 point of SAN.\par
If the SAN roll succeeded, there is a chance that the positive attention from the community may convert into an increase in status. Make a second D100 roll and compare it to current \b Community Bond rating\'d75\b0 . If the roll is \i higher\i0  than the target, the Community Bond value improves:\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\f2\'b7\tab\f1 If the original SAN roll was a \b normal success\b0 : +1 to bond value\par
\f2\'b7\tab\f1 If the original SAN roll was a \b critical success\b0 : +2 to bond value\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 The causes of the increase or decrease in status should be described, along with their impact.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 8.2.4\tab Back to Nature\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1 Your Protagonist can spend time in contemplative seclusion, minimizing stress, distractions, and obligations. This isn\rquote t a holiday; it\rquote s extended time alone, or mostly alone, in an environment that\rquote s physically active but places few other demands on the Protagonist. This reduces one Bond (either Individual or Community) by 1 as you let other responsibilities lapse. Roll a SAN test. Success adds 1D4 SAN, or 4 for a critical (up to your \b Recovery SAN\b0 ). Failure adds 1 SAN. A fumble costs 1D4 SAN. Describe the impact of this time alone.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 8.2.5\tab Establish a New Individual Bond\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1 Your Protagonist may attempt to create a new Individual Bond with a character. This is not done lightly. It means this new character is developing into an essential, important part of your Protagonist\rquote s life. Attempt a \b CHA\'d75\b0  test. Success establishes a new Individual Bond with a score equal to half your Protagonist\rquote s CHA (round up). Unfortunately, devoting so much attention to the new Bond reduces the value of one other Bond \endash  either reduce an Individual Bond by 1D4 or a Community Bond by 1.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 8.2.6\tab Establish a New Community Bond\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1 Your Protagonist attempts to establish membership in a new community and assert some kind of status within its \lquote pecking order\rquote . You might do this because you have just arrived in a new place, or because you wish to take on a position of standing within a group (e.g., an elite order) that provides social benefits. Getting accepted to a position of trust within a community is not easy. Attempt a \b CHA\'d75\b0  test. Success establishes a new Community Bond with a score equal to \b half\b0  your Protagonist\rquote s Permanent Resources rating (round up). Devoting energy to currying the favor needed to establish the new Bond reduces the value of one other Bond \endash  either reduce an Individual Bond by 1D4 or a (different) Community Bond by 1.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 8.2.7\tab Get Help With Mental Illnesses\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1 Depending on where and when your game is set, Protagonists may have the option of accessing professional mental health services to try to overcome the ill-effects accrued through traumatic experiences. Prior to the mid-20th Century, such services were very primitive and arguably more damaging to sanity than curative. The GM will be the final arbiter as to whether reliable and high-quality psychotherapy services are available. However, even in settings where no such facilities exist there are still ways to get help in more old-fashioned ways.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Therapy\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 If your Protagonist chooses to enlist a clinical therapist to deal with his or her psychological damage, he or she is committing to an ongoing process requiring honesty and commitment. \par
Your Protagonist must decide whether to truthfully tell the therapist what caused the SAN loss. \par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\f2\'b7\tab\f1 If your Protagonist tells the truth, there are risks. If the SAN loss came from confronting the Cthulhu Mythos, your therapist might diagnose your Protagonist as suffering from schizophrenia. Alternatively, if the therapist \i believes\i0  your Protagonist\rquote s account, he or she may in turn lose SAN from the shocking details they reveal. \par
\pard\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1 The outcomes of therapy are determined by a roll against the therapist\rquote s \b Psychoanalyze\b0  skill. If your Protagonist described unnatural events and the therapist thinks they\rquote re delusions, that skill is halved. If the roll fumbles, your Protagonist loses 1 SAN. If it succeeds, your Protagonist regains 1D6 SAN (or 6 with a critical success), up to his or her \b Recovery SAN\b0 .\par
If your Protagonist shares tales of terrible, illegal violence and it sounds like further violence is imminent, the therapist may report it to the authorities. Whether that happens is entirely up to the GM.\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\f2\'b7\tab\f1 If, on the other hand, your Protagonist \i doesn\rquote t\i0  tell the therapist the truth, healing is limited. Make a roll against the therapist\rquote s \b Psychoanalyze\b0  skill. If it fumbles, your Protagonist loses 1 SAN. If it succeeds, your Protagonist regains 1D4 SAN (or 4 for a critical success), up to his or her \b Recovery SAN\b0 .\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 If your Protagonist suffers from a disorder, a critical success with the therapist\rquote s roll cures it (whether your Protagonist told the truth or not). Your Protagonist also develops a Bond with the therapist equal to half your Protagonist\rquote s CHA (or add 1D4 to it if your Protagonist already has that Bond, up to the Protagonist\rquote s CHA). He or she also loses points from another bond of your choice (1D4 from one individual Bond or 1 from a Community Bond). Write a note saying \ldblquote cured\rdblquote  next to the disorder on the character sheet \emdash  but do not erase it. The next time you gain a disorder, you must roll another SAN test. If that fails, the \ldblquote cured\rdblquote  disorder returns in full force alongside the new one.\par
Regardless of whether the rolls result in improvements, the long hours spent with an empathetic person reduces one Bond (either Individual or Community) by 1 as you let other responsibilities lapse.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s4\sb40\sl276\slmult1\cf1\i\f0 Talking it Out\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\i0\f1 Even if no clinical psychotherapy is available to your Protagonist, there is still the time-honored method of healing a damaged mind through sharing one\rquote s burden with an empathic person who one knows and trusts. This other person might be a spiritual adviser, a folk-psychiatrists, or just a kind-hearted fellow member of the community that is willing to reassure you.\par
Being helped through the process of recovering from mental trauma works in a similar way to therapy although takes a lot longer and has less certain outcomes. As with therapy there are risks to sharing detailed accounts of the events that caused the original SAN loss, both to the empathic person (who could take SAN from the account) and to the Protagonist (if the other individual alerts others).\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\f2\'b7\tab\f1 As with formal therapy, the effectiveness of folk remedies is determined through skill rolls against the \b Psychoanalyze\b0  skill (or an alternate skill substituted by the GM as fits the game\rquote s setting). The difference is that for any benefit to be achieved, the empathic person must succeed in two consecutive rolls.\par
\pard\fi-357\li714\sa60\sl276\slmult1\f2\'b7\tab\f1 If the Protagonist has not been truthful in relating their story, they can still gain some benefit: a pair of consecutive successful rolls will give them 1D2 SAN back (2 with a critical success), up to his or her POW \'d7 5. If the Protagonist was truthful, the reward is 1D3 SAN (3 with a critical success), to the same maximum.\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1 For a Protagonist to have a disorder cured through folk remedies, the empathic listener must get two consecutive critical successes on their rolls. If that occurs, it functions in the same way to a therapist making a critical success. \par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 As with therapists, the hours spent with the empathic listener has the inevitable impact that one other bond (either Individual or Community) is reduced by 1 as you let responsibilities lapse. If the long conversations led to a disorder being cured, you will automatically develop or strengthen an Individual Bond with the empathic listener as noted above for successful therapy outcomes \endash  but at the cost of another bond becoming weaker.\lang3081\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb120\sl276\slmult1\cf2\lang1033\b\f0 8.2.8\tab Improve a Skill or Stat\par
\pard\sa120\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1 By training or studying extensively, your Protagonist can try to boost a stat or a skill. This reduces one Bond (either Individual or Community) by 1 as you let other responsibilities lapse. \par
Describe what your Protagonist is doing to improve the stat or skill: \lang3081 poring over crumbling books for INT or a skill, lifting weights for STR, meditating to strengthen self-discipline for POW, loitering in a club or attending a leadership institute for CHA, working with one's personal physician to regain stat points permanently lost from an injury, etc.\lang1033  \par
If you wish to gain points in a skill you don\rquote t already possess and which has a Base Chance of 0%, you can \ul only\ulnone  do this if you are being trained by someone who has at least 20% in that skill. Under no circumstances can the Unnatural skill be improved through training.\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 Attempt a test of the stat \'d7 5 or the skill. If the test fails, your Protagonist has improved. Add 3D6 percentage points to the skill (to a maximum of 99%) or one point to the stat (to a maximum of 18).\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb120\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 8.2.9\tab Personal Motivation\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1 Your Protagonist indulges in the things that he or she finds meaningful. This reduces one Bond (either Individual or Community) by 1 as you let other responsibilities lapse. Roll a SAN test. Success adds 1 SAN, or 1D4 for a critical (up to your Protagonist\rquote s \b Recovery SAN\b0 ). A fumble costs 1 SAN.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb120\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 8.2.10\tab Accounts of the Cthulhu Mythos / Learning Rituals\par
\pard\cf0\b0\f1 Your Protagonist may have unearthed records \endash  e.g., \lang3081 ancient tomes, journals or miscellaneous manuscripts\lang1033  \endash  which claim to contain wisdom about the Cthulhu Mythos forces which haunt the world. He or she can devote time to trying to delve into such accounts or trying to learn the arcane rituals they describe. See \b\caps MADDENING Revelations\b0\caps0  on page \lang3081 81\lang1033  for more on how such research is performed.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\pagebb\s1\sb480\sl276\slmult1\cf1\b\f0\fs28 PART II: GAME MODERATOR RESOURCES\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1\fs22 This section consists of a series of resources which are designed to help a Game Moderator design exciting and dangerous scenarios to challenge a Protagonist Group. \par
\pard\keep\keepn\s1\fi-432\li432\sb480\sl276\slmult1\cf1\b\f0\fs28 9.0\tab Maddening Revelations\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1\fs22 A common feature of Cthulhu Mythos fiction is the existence of musty old tomes which describe the \lquote truth\rquote  about mankind\rquote s perilous place in the universe, and the powers thirsting for cosmic upheaval. In the \lang3081 Jazz Age\lang1033  such revelations might be found buried in \lang3081 ancient tomes, journals or miscellaneous manuscripts\lang1033 . Alternatively, the secret knowledge might be passed down from generation-to-generation through spoken tales and mystic traditions.\par
Revelatory accounts and the secret information they contain can, if you wish, be important parts of your \i Cthulhu Eternal\i0  game. Some of the revelations might describe supernatural powers or \ldblquote magickal effects\rdblquote  that Protagonists might be able to utilize to fight back the shadows. Often these will require they perform time-consuming rituals drawn from mystical traditions.\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s2\fi-576\li576\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0\fs26 9.1\tab Researching the Mythos\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1\fs22 If you as Game Moderator want to include a form of revelatory information in your game, there are a few factors to consider:\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\f2\'b7\tab\f1 How will the Protagonist\rquote s locate it?\par
\f2\'b7\tab\f1 What skill rolls are needed to read it (or view it, or otherwise access its information)?\par
\f2\'b7\tab\f1 How long does it take to study the information before it is understood?\par
\f2\'b7\tab\f1 Does the information cause a Sanity Loss to those who learn it?\par
\f2\'b7\tab\f1 Does understanding the revelations cause an increase in skills?\par
\f2\'b7\tab\f1 Does it impart some other benefit, such as the chance to learn a magickal ritual?\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1 Mythos accounts offer one of the few ways in which Protagonists may increase their rating in the \b Unnatural\b0  skill. Each has an associated amount of Unnatural skill gain that it might potentially impart \'85 if only the Protagonist is able to see past its disordered jumble of insane ideas. Simple accounts of the Cthulhu Mythos might impart just a few points (+1 to +3 perhaps) while weighty records (like those immortalized in the infamous \i Necronomicon\i0 ) might offer the reader thorough and dangerous insight (+15 or more points of increase in \b Unnatural\b0 ).\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 9.1.1\tab Finding Information\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1 If the \lquote tome\rquote  (or other information source) is hidden away or stored as part of a vast collection, Protagonists may need to exercise a range of skills to track it down. Or maybe interpersonal skills will allow them to get directions to it from people who are knowledgeable about the collection?\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 9.1.2\tab Accessing and Understanding the Contents\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1 If the item is expressed in a language other than the common vernacular, understanding it might require a relevant \lang3081\b Foreign Language\lang1033  \b0 test. This is especially true if the information is expressed in archaic or highly specialized language.\par
Other possibilities:\par
\pard\fi-360\li720\sa200\sl276\slmult1\lang1024\f2\'b7\tab\lang3081\f1 If the knowledge locked up in the account is highly contextualized on esoteric systems of thought it might also require an \b Occult\b0  test. \par
\lang1024\f2\'b7\tab\lang3081\f1 If it is so full of references back to antiquated knowledge that it can\rquote t readily be understood, perhaps a \b History\b0  or \b Anthropology\b0  test might be required. \par
\lang1024\f2\'b7\tab\lang3081\f1 On the other hand, if the knowledge is closely tied to people, places, folklore and events from a particular geography then maybe a relevant \b Regional Lore\b0  test may be needed.\par
\lang1024\f2\'b7\tab\lang3081\f1 If the information is written using a cipher a \b Science (Codes and Ciphers)\b0  test might be called for, or perhaps a roll against a relevant \b Military Training\b0  specialialization.\lang1033\par
\pard\keep\keepn\s3\fi-720\li720\sb200\sl276\slmult1\cf2\b\f0 9.1.3\tab Immersion\par
\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\cf0\b0\f1 To the layperson, an account of the Cthulhu Mythos looks like nothing more than a random collection of disjointed thoughts, none of them imparting any real meaning. This is because most people have no prior experience of the Unnatural and thus have no reason to think that the gibbering ravings might be something meaningful.\par
If the Protagonist undertaking the research has an \b Unnatural\b0  skill rating of 0, he or she will be likewise unconvinced. Such an individual will be unable to become sufficiently \lquote immersed\rquote  in the account\rquote s buried secrets to learn anything useful at all.\par
On the other hand, a researcher with skill in \b Unnatural\b0  may be able to see beyond the disconnected rantings and perceive the implied secrets. This requires an \b Immersion test:\b0  a roll against the Protagonist\rquote s current \ul Unnatural skill \'d7 10\ulnone  with a negative modifier based on the account\rquote s weightiness (measured by the amount of potential additional Unnatural skill it may afford the cautious reader). \par
