\pard\intbl\sa120\cf0\b0\f1 During a translation the GM might need to invent some game statistics for a creature\rquote s special vulnerability. Here are a few ideas that can be used as starting points for new inventions.\par
\pard\intbl\sa60\b Hates the Light: \b0 The entity takes damage from exposure to light. Bright light inflicts 1 HP per turn; bright and dazzling light inflicts 3D6. Full daylight reduces the entity to a pile of grey ash. This damage ignores armor.\par
\b Poisoned by <Substance>: \b0 The entity\rquote s metabolism is particularly susceptible to a common earthly substance. Whenever the entity comes into direct physical contact with the substance it must make a \b CON\'d75\b0  test; if it fails, the entity suffers Lethality 10% damage. \par
\pard\intbl\sa120\b Susceptible to Fire:\b0  Fire inflicts \i double\i0  damage to the entity. This damage ignores armor.\cell\row\pard\sa200\sl276\slmult1\par
